<text>
<body>

<div1 type="postcard">

<div2>
<figure><ab>Grand Canyon National Park<lb/>
Arizona<lb/>
On East Rim Drive<lb/>
East of Yavapai Point<lb/>
Picturesque old juniper on brink of Grand Canyon. The green Expanses of Kaibab National Forest hem the Canyon's Rims with dense growths of Alpine trees and shrubs.</ab></figure>

<opener>
<dateline>June 10</dateline>
</opener>
<p>Dear John: &#8212; Yesterday Nita &amp; I completed a <unclear>two day</unclear> 18 mile mule back trip into the depths of the Canyon. It is beautiful beyond the telling. As we tracked through that terrific country, I could not help but think of Jed Smith &amp; his crossing of the Sierra Nevada.</p>

<closer><salute>Affectionately,</salute>
<signed>Slade</signed>
</closer>
</div2>
